Convoy escorting police officer Caroline Kangogo’s body for burial at Nyawa, Elgeyo Marakwet County. [Peter Ochieng, Standard]  The body of Corporal Caroline Kangogo has left Iten County Referral Hospital mortuary for burial at her parents' home in Anin, Elgeyo Marakwet.  Kangogo was found dead two weeks ago in a bathroom at her parents' homestead.    A postmortem conducted by Chief Government Pathologist Johansen Oduor indicated that Kangogo died of a gunshot wound that entered through her right chin, exiting through the left side of her head.  Kangogo died of gunshot wound- Government pathologist says  Caroline Kangogo’s autopsy today  Caroline Kangogo’s autopsy rescheduled to Tuesday  Kangogo’s burial postponed after stand-off The convoy escorting the body snaked its way through Kerio escarpments to Anin. Kangogo is suspected to have killed police officer John Ogweno in Nakuru and businessesman Peter Ngegwa in Juja, Kiambu County.  Hundreds of boda boda riders and tens of motorists from Iten Town are escorting the hearse ferrying the body.  Convoy escorting police officer Caroline Kangogo’s body for burial at Nyawa, Elgeyo Marakwet County. [Peter Ochieng, Standard]  Relatives and friends view the body of the late Caroline Chemutai Kangogo at Nyawa, Elgeyo Marakwet. [Peter Ochieng, Standard]      By Antony Gitonga  | 2 hours ago By Gilbert Kimutai | 3 hours ago By Nderitu Gichure | 12 hours ago By Robert Kiplagat  | 12 hours ago